issue.title: bugCD2
Packaging: `ImportError: cannot import name '__version__'` after `pip install -U aider-chat`
issue.body:
### Description

After updating to `aider-chat==0.86.0` via `pip install -U aider-chat`, the application fails to start with an `ImportError`.

This appears to be a recurring packaging issue (see #1045, #242, #209) where the `aider/__init__.py` file is empty in the distributed package, causing the application to crash on startup.

### Traceback

```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin/aider", line 3, in <module>
    from aider.main import main
  File "/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/lib/python3.12/site-packages/aider/main.py", line 21, in <module>
    from aider import __version__, models, urls, utils
  File "/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/lib/python3.12/site-packages/aider/models.py", line 19, in <module>
    from aider import __version__
ImportError: cannot import name '__version__' from 'aider' (/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/lib/python3.12/site-packages/aider/__init__.py)
```

### Root Cause

The `__init__.py` file at `/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/lib/python3.12/site-packages/aider/__init__.py` is empty after a fresh installation/update, leading to the `ImportError`.

### Workaround

The issue can be resolved by populating the `__init__.py` file to dynamically load the version from the package's metadata. This is a robust, standard practice.

```python
# /data/data/com.termux/files/usr/lib/python3.12/site-packages/aider/__init__.py
import importlib.metadata
__version__ = importlib.metadata.version("aider-chat")
```

### Environment

- **Package Version**: `aider-chat==0.86.0`
- **Operating System**: Android (via Termux)
- **Python**: 3.12

issue.title: Implement a singleton resource representation of the current user
issue.body:
## Task Description

Implement a **`/api/me`** endpoint that returns combined information about the currently authenticated user.
The endpoint should extract user identity from the JWT token, fetch both core user data (e.g., email) and additional profile data (e.g., nickname, avatar, bio), and return it in a single DTO.
This ensures the frontend can display all "My Profile" details using one request.

### Type

* [x] Feature

### Checklist

* [ ] Code implemented
* [ ] Tests (if needed)
* [ ] Committed and pushed
* [ ] PR opened and reviewed

### Additional Notes

* Reuse existing JWT authentication logic to extract the user (e.g., email or ID).
* Create a unified DTO to control which fields are exposed (combine user and profile data).
* Consider null-safe handling of optional profile fields (e.g., if a user hasnt set up their profile yet).
* Example endpoint: `GET /api/me`
* Related future work: implement `PUT /api//me` for updating profile info separately.
* Reference: [[Spring Security - Getting the current authenticated user](https://www.baeldung.com/get-user-in-spring-security)](https://www.baeldung.com/get-user-in-spring-security)

casuarina: Use libhidlbase_shim instead of libhidlbase-v32 for vendor.fpsensor.hardware.fpsensorhidlsvc@2.0.so

Using libhidlbase-v32 just straight up crashing the library and cause null
pointer dereference in Lineage fingerprint AIDL HAL. On the other side,
libhidlbase_shim doesn't do that, and yet still provides the shim we wanted.

Change-Id: I84722863249ffec3e47ba467b0d2c1e187049f3c

casuarina: init: move wcnss-service to late_start

* wcnss-service is in charge of copying your wcnss ini from /system to
  /data where framework reads it. If /data is encrypted, or being
  encrypted, this can't happen. Move it to late_start so it tries to run
  after encrpytion and mount has happened.
